  "local_port": 56092,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I open a Demat account with SBI and do online trading?",
  "response": "Opening a **Demat account** with **State Bank of India (SBI)** and starting **online trading** is a straightforward process. Here's a step-by-step guide:\n\n---\n\n### **Step 1: Choose the Right Account**\nSBI offers **2-in-1 (Trading + Demat)** or **3-in-1 (Bank + Trading + Demat)** accounts. Choose based on your convenience:\n- **2-in-1 Account**: Demat + Trading Account.\n- **3-in-1 Account**: SBI Bank Account + Demat + Trading Account.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 2: Check Eligibility**\n- You must be **18 years or older**.\n- Have a valid **PAN card**.\n- Have an SBI savings account (if opting for 3-in-1 account).\n\n---\n\n### **Step 3: Gather Required Documents**\n1. **Identity Proof**: PAN card, Aadhaar card, Passport, etc.\n2. **Address Proof**: Aadhaar card, Passport, Utility bill, etc.\n3. **Passport-sized Photographs**.\n4. **Income Proof** (for trading account): Salary slip, ITR, etc. (optional for some cases).\n5. **Cancelled Cheque** (for bank account details).\n\n---\n\n### **Step 4: Apply for the Demat Account**\nYou can apply **online** or **offline**:\n\n#### **Online Process**:\n1. Visit SBI\u2019s dedicated portal for Demat accounts: **[SBI Demat Account](https://sbi.co.in/demat)**.\n2. Click on **\u201cOpen Your Demat Account\u201d**.\n3. Fill in the required details (personal, KYC, and bank account information).\n4. Upload scanned copies of your documents (PAN, Aadhaar, photograph, etc.).\n5. Complete the **e-KYC** process using your Aadhaar OTP.\n6. Pay the applicable charges (if any).\n7. Submit the application.\n\n#### **Offline Process**:\n1. Visit your nearest **SBI branch** or **SBI Securities branch**.\n2. Collect the Demat account application form.\n3. Fill in the details and attach the required documents.\n4. Submit the form to the branch representative.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 5: Activate Your Account**\n1. Once your application is processed, you\u2019ll receive your **Demat account number** and **login credentials**.\n2. Activate your account by logging in and setting a password.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 6: Start Online Trading**\n1. Download the **SBI Securities app** or visit their trading portal: **[SBI Securities](https://www.sbisecurities.in)**.\n2. Log in using your credentials.\n3. Add funds to your trading account (if required).\n4. Start buying and selling shares, mutual funds, or other securities.\n\n---\n\n### **Charges and Fees**\n- **Account Opening Charges**: Usually \u20b90 to \u20b9850 (varies based on promotional offers).\n- **Annual Maintenance Charges (AMC)**: \u20b9300 to \u20b9750 + GST.\n- **Transaction Charges**: Brokerage fees and other applicable charges.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Online Trading**\n- **Research** the stocks or securities before investing.\n- Use **stop-loss orders** to minimize risks.\n- Regularly monitor your portfolio.\n\n---\n\nFor further assistance, you can contact **SBI Securities Customer Care** or visit their website.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
